'''Hamdy Fathy Abdelhalim Abdelfattah''' ({{langx|ar|حمدي فتحي عبد الحليم عبد الفتاح}}; born 29 September 1994) is an Egyptian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Wakrah SC|Al-Wakrah]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

==Club career==
Fathy began his career with [[Ala'ab Damanhour SC|Ala'ab Damanhour]] before moving to [[ENPPI Club|Enppi]] in 2015 and later joining [[Petrojet FC|Petrojet]] on loan. In 2019, he signed with [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] and remained with the club until 2023, when he transferred to Qatari side [[Al-Wakrah SC|Al-Wakrah]].

=== 2025: Loan to Al Ahly ===
In December 2024, it was announced that he would return to Al Ahly on loan to participate in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/51/537032/Sports/Egyptian-Football/Ahly-secure-loan-deal-for-Hamdi-Fathi-from-AlWakra.aspx |title=Ahly secure loan deal for Hamdi Fathi from Al-Wakrah SC for the 2025 FIFA Club World Cup |publisher=Ahram Online |date=15 December 2024 }}</ref>

==International career==
On 14 October 2019, Fathy made his international debut and scored the only goal of the match in a 1–0 win against [[Botswana national football team|Botswana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=860747&o=n3107844|script-title=ar:حمدي فتحي يضع بصمته الأولى مع منتخب مصر|website=Kooora|language=Arabic|date=14 October 2019}}</ref> Hamdy featured in the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021 AFCON]] final match against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Afcon 2021: Egypt XI to face Senegal – Salah, Elneny start, Ashour in for suspended Kamal {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gh/lists/afcon-2021-egypt-xi-to-face-senegal-salah-elneny-start-ashour-in-/bltbabcf03e09d636c6#csbd32c2ed1f492e6b|access-date=6 February 2022|website=www.goal.com}}</ref>

On 2 December 2025, Fathy was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

